ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# Subscription Price IDs (price_...), NOT Product IDs (prod_...).
# Stripe Dashboard → Product → click your product → under "Pricing" copy each Price's API ID.
STRIPE_PRICE_STARTER=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_ULTRA=price_...
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
# On Vercel, set this to your production URL (https://yourdomain.com). Otherwise request origin / VERCEL_URL is used where applicable.
# Comma-separated admin emails (server-only). Must match the user's login email.
ADMIN_EMAILS=you@example.com

# --- Production (Vercel + Supabase + Stripe) quick checklist ---
# 1) Vercel: import repo, add every variable above in Project → Settings → Environment Variables (Production).
# 2) NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL: set to https://<your-vercel-domain-or-custom-domain> (no trailing slash).
# 3) Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → URL: set Site URL to the same. Add redirect URLs: same + http://localhost:3000 for local dev.
# 4) Supabase: run SQL migrations (supabase/migrations) on the linked project; confirm Storage bucket "part-images" exists.
# 5) Stripe Dashboard → Developers → Webhooks → Add endpoint: https://<your-domain>/api/stripe/webhook
#    Subscribe to: checkout.session.completed, customer.subscription.updated. Paste signing secret into STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET.
# 6) Stripe: use Live mode keys (sk_live_..., pk_live_...) and live Price IDs (price_...) in Production env on Vercel.
